5|$|Globally, as of 2009, {{approximately}} 60% {{of those}} who are married and able to have children use birth control. How frequently different methods are used varies widely between countries. The most common method in the developed world is condoms and oral contraceptives, while in Africa it is oral contraceptives and in Latin America and Asia it is <b>sterilization.</b> In the developing world overall, 35% of birth control is via female <b>sterilization,</b> 30% is via IUDs, 12% is via oral contraceptives, 11% is via condoms, and 4% is via male <b>sterilization.</b>|$|E
